.TH "rtcalc" "1" "June 2026" "rtcalc release 1.28.8"
.SH NAME
rtcalc \- Interactive CLI math program
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[CR]rtcalc\f[R] [flags]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Takes in user input interactively and in real time, calculating the
formula provided by the user and outputting it.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[CR]help\f[R]
Show a help menu, providing basic usage info.
.TP
\f[CR]prompt=[str]\f[R]
Replace default shell prompt with user provided one.
Note that the space beetwen input and prompt is NOT automatically
provided.
.TP
\f[CR]syntax\-highlighting\f[R]
Enable input syntax highlighting, coloring different components of the
input.
.TP
\f[CR]precision=[num]\f[R]
Sets the printed result\(cqs floating point precision to a user set
value.
.TP
\f[CR]define:[name]=[val]\f[R]
Defines a new variable of name with a value ([value]).
The value field is calculated in the same way that a formula would
interactively, meaning that even functions apply.
And naturally, you may also use variables defined before in the formula.
.SH BASIC USAGE
After starting the program, type in the formula to be calculated,
following basic math principles.
The program will automatically error out on invalid formulas or syntax.
.SH SYNTAX AND EXAMPLES
Type in two operands and an operator.
.PP
\f[CR]x + y\f[R]
.PP
The program supports more than one operand, as long as there are enough
operators.
.PP
\f[CR]x + y \- z\f[R]
.PP
Each operator has an order of operations, that being:
.PP
\f[CR]+\f[R], \f[CR]\-\f[R]: Third priority.
.PP
\f[CR]*\f[R], \f[CR]/\f[R], \f[CR]%\f[R]: Second priority.
.PP
\f[CR]\(ha\f[R]: First priority.
.PP
You may introduce parentheses.
.PP
\f[CR]x * y \(ha (z + z)\f[R]
.PP
Parentheses may be nested.
.PP
\f[CR]x + (x + (y * (z + x)))\f[R]
.PP
Functions are implemented.
Their results are treated as operands.
.PP
\f[CR]sqrt[x] + y\f[R]
.PP
You may write formulas inside of functions.
.PP
\f[CR]sqrt[x * y]\f[R]
.PP
Defined variables may be integrated seamlessly, being treated as regular
operands.
.PP
\f[CR]{x} * {y}\f[R]
.PP
Specific formulas will required two arguments.
Separate each with a semicolon.
.PP
\f[CR]logx[x ; y]\f[R]
.SH OPERATORS
.TP
\f[CR]x + y\f[R]
Perform addition.
.TP
\f[CR]x \- y\f[R]
Perform subtraction.
.TP
\f[CR]x * y\f[R]
Perform addition.
.TP
\f[CR]x / y\f[R]
Perform addition.
.TP
\f[CR]x % y\f[R]
Perform division, and return the rest.
.TP
\f[CR]x \(ha y\f[R]
Perform exponentiation.
.SH FUNCTIONS
.SS Trigonometric
Note that all trigonometric functions return in radians.
.TP
\f[CR]sin[x]\f[R]
Perform the sine of `x'.
.TP
\f[CR]cos[x]\f[R]
Perform the cosine of `x'.
.TP
\f[CR]tan[x]\f[R]
Perform the tangent of `x'.
.TP
\f[CR]sinh[x]\f[R]
Perform the hyperbolic sine of `x'.
.TP
\f[CR]cosh[x]\f[R]
Perform the hyperbolic cosine of `x'.
.TP
\f[CR]tan[x]\f[R]
Perform the hyperbolic tangent of `x'.
.TP
\f[CR]asin[x]\f[R]
Perform the reverse sine of `x'.
.TP
\f[CR]acos[x]\f[R]
Perform the reverse cosine of `x'.
.TP
\f[CR]atan[x]\f[R]
Perform the reverse tangent of `x'.
.TP
\f[CR]asinh[x]\f[R]
Perform the reverse hyperbolic sine of `x'.
.TP
\f[CR]acosh[x]\f[R]
Perform the reverse hyperbolic cosine of `x'.
.TP
\f[CR]atanh[x]\f[R]
Perform the reverse hyperbolic tangent of `x'.
.TP
\f[CR]atan2[x]\f[R]
Get the angle theta from the conversion of rectangular coordinates (x,
y) to polar coordinates (r, theta).
.TP
\f[CR]csc[x]\f[R]
Perform the cosecant of `x'.
.TP
\f[CR]sec[x]\f[R]
Perform the secant of `x'.
.TP
\f[CR]cot[x]\f[R]
Perform the cotangent of `x'.
.TP
\f[CR]csch[x]\f[R]
Perform the hyperbolic cosecant of `x'.
.TP
\f[CR]sech[x]\f[R]
Perform the hyperbolic secant of `x'.
.TP
\f[CR]coth[x]\f[R]
Perform the hyperbolic cotangent of `x'.
.SS Conversion
.TP
\f[CR]deg[x]\f[R]
Convert radians to degrees.
.TP
\f[CR]rad[x]\f[R]
Convert degrees to radians.
.SS Rounding
.TP
\f[CR]floor[x]\f[R]
Get the floor of `x'.
.TP
\f[CR]ceil[x]\f[R]
Get the ceiling of `x'.
.TP
\f[CR]trunc[x]\f[R]
Get the integer part of `x'.
.TP
\f[CR]round[x]\f[R]
Round `x' to the nearest integer.
.TP
\f[CR]rndflr[x, y]\f[R]
Round `x\(cqs floor to \(cqy'.
.TP
\f[CR]rndcei[x, y]\f[R]
Round `x\(cqs ceiling to \(cqy'.
.SS Exponential
.TP
\f[CR]sqrt[x]\f[R]
Perform the square root of `x'.
.TP
\f[CR]cbrt[x]\f[R]
Perform the cube root of `x'.
.TP
\f[CR]log[x]\f[R]
Perform the natural logarithm of `x'.
.TP
\f[CR]log10[x]\f[R]
Perform the base 10 logarithm of `x'.
.TP
\f[CR]log2[x]\f[R]
Perform the base 2 logarithm of `x'.
.TP
\f[CR]logx[x, y]\f[R] (aka \f[CR]log_x()\f[R])
Perform the base `y' logarithm of `x'.
.TP
\f[CR]exp[x]\f[R]
Perform the value of E \(ha `x'.
.TP
\f[CR]exp2[x]\f[R]
Perform the value of 2 \(ha `x'.
.TP
\f[CR]pow[x, y]\f[R]
Get the result of `x' to the power of `y'.
